INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (13,5,'2017-01-11 20:29:39','2017-01-11 20:29:39','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Welcome to my WordPress adventure!Can you feel the stoke?!! I\'m officially switching over from the tired old html website to this snazzy new WP site. I\'ll try to keep up with my blog in the near future.For now I\'ll take all the criticisms and compliments you will throw at me.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">But seriously, speaking of compliments..</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium\" src=\"https://media.giphy.com/media/upIgwkDSvpAWY/giphy.gif\" width=\"575\" height=\"404\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Haha! I just couldn\'t resist.. :D</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Cheers!</p>','Woo Hoo! It\'s Wordpress!','','publish','open','open','','woo-hoo-its-wordpress','','','2017-03-03 10:21:48','2017-03-03 18:21:48','',0,'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/?p=13',0,'post','',0),(15,5,'2017-01-11 20:32:33','2017-01-11 20:32:33','<div class=\"crayon-plain-wrap\">\r\n<div id=\"crayon-58811faf85d42226995939-1\" class=\"crayon-line\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I\'m a front-end &amp; WordPress developer, blogger, artist and adventurer.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I\'m a free spirit with many interests and passions.\r\nI love new tech and grand ideas that are helping people to evolve towards a more sustainable relationship with our planet.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I\'m passionate about green living, camping, hiking and protecting this beautiful planet. I\'ll share things like cool new camping and trekking gear, awesome green living gadgets and ideas, essential oil recipesand delicious foods I like to bring outdoors. I\'ll also be sharing my ideas and thoughts about some of the big issues we face in this world and some of the solutions available, as well as some of my adventures.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Cheers!</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Hi, I\'m Natalie! I love building websites and adventures.','','publish','closed','closed','','homepage','','','2017-03-05 22:44:05','2017-03-06 06:44:05','',0,'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/?page_id=15',0,'page','',0),(20,5,'2017-01-11 18:06:34','2017-01-12 02:06:34','','Blog','','publish','closed','closed','','blog','','','2017-01-11 18:06:34','2017-01-12 02:06:34','',0,'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/?page_id=20',0,'page','',0),(47330,5,'2017-01-16 14:15:27','2017-01-16 22:15:27','<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-47582 alignright\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nat6.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Hello, and welcome to Natalie Rose.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I\'m Natalie, a front-end and WordPress developer, artist and outdoor enthusiast. I\'m a busy 30-something millennial currently living on the beautiful west coast of Canada. I have many passions and hobbies and work hard so I can play even harder! I\'m in love with this amazing planet and strive to spend as much time as possible exploring the wild nooks and spectacularvistas nature has to offer. I love hiking and camping and I\'mworking towards challenging myself on some longer through hiking adventures.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Naturally, I have a great interest in ecology, biology and conservation and strive to live as environmentally consciously as possible. I have a burning passion to protect the wild places and to help humanity live more in cinque with nature. There are so many incredible inventions, technologies, and new ideas discovered every day that I have great hope for the future! I believe the challenges we face these days are great, but with love and co-operation we can not only overcome these obstacles but evolve and thrive! My mission is to spread awareness, innovation, solutions and lots of love!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I\'m also a creative soul and love to work with my hands and heart. I enjoy things like painting and woodworking, and the old-school homey arts such as gardening, farming, foraging, canning, and creating my own health and beauty products out of plant materialsand essential oils.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Another passion of mine isto help people reach their professional dreams. As a front-end and WordPress developer I love to create beautiful, easy to use and fully functional websites. I work with amazing people; from bloggers to business owners and thoroughly enjoy digging into the deep cavernsof code to help make websites that stand out among the crowd. I can build websites from scratch and have experience editing and updating existing websites and dynamic web applications. I\'m proficient in HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, JQuery, Git, Github, WordPress and Responsive design.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Does your website lose ease and functionality when accessed on mobile or tablet? There are so many websites out there that are so poorly designed and frustrating to use on a mobile, don\'t be one of them andlose out on customers or clients because of a bad mobile design. I can update an existing static website to a responsive design that works well across all browsers and platforms. Are you tired of html and want to switch over to the wonderful world of WordPress? I can make the switch over for you or help you with the process. Do you want something fresh, dynamic and unique? I can modify WordPress themes to make your website truly one of a kind and exactly the way you want.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Drop me a line and I\'ll see what I can do for you!</p>\r\n\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: left;\">[wpforms id=\"47560\"]</h6>','About Me','','publish','closed','closed','','about-me','','','2017-03-05 22:43:50','2017-03-06 06:43:50','',0,'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/?page_id=47330',0,'page','',0),(47336,5,'2017-02-02 05:13:29','2017-02-02 05:13:29','','Facebook','','publish','closed','closed','','facebook','','','2017-03-03 09:46:31','2017-03-03 17:46:31','',0,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/?p=47336',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(47338,5,'2017-02-02 05:13:30','2017-02-02 05:13:30','','Github','','publish','closed','closed','','github','','','2017-03-03 09:46:31','2017-03-03 17:46:31','',0,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/?p=47338',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(47446,5,'2017-01-26 16:28:36','2017-01-27 00:28:36','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Finally! The day I have been waiting for is almost at hand! It\'s time to take this baby and shove her out into the cold vastness of the interwebs. Soon I shall have actual content and interesting things to share with my non-existent viewers.. but for now it\'s time to celebrate!! Three cheers for the launch! Hip Hip Hooray!</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium\" src=\"https://media.giphy.com/media/1PMVNNKVIL8Ig/giphy.gif\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Time to celebrate!</p>','She\'s going live!','','publish','open','open','','shes-going-live','','','2017-03-03 10:20:22','2017-03-03 18:20:22','',0,'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/?p=47446',0,'post','',0),(47486,5,'2017-02-01 10:51:38','2017-02-01 18:51:38','<img class=\" wp-image-47483 aligncenter\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/homeless-300x160.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"521\" height=\"278\" />\n\nI was on a hike the other day with some good friends when something was said that really struck a nerve.\n\nWe were having a discussion about politics and it was mentioned that a certain party\'s views were \"too socialist\" and that he \"didn\'t want to have to pay for people that are just too lazy to get a job or help themselves.\" I tried to explain that laziness usually has absolutely nothing to do with poverty and homelessness, but of course I had a hard time explaining my pointswhile struggling to clamber my way up a steep slope.\n\nHe\'s an intelligent guy, and we usually have good conversations, so how could he have this skewed(in my opinion) viewpoint? Reflecting later on I realized that actually a lot of people share this view. Here is my attempt to shed a little light on this complicated issue.\n\nFirst off, you can\'t just lump everyone into the same category. There are many types of people from varying circumstances that make up the homeless population. There are the working homeless, people who actually do have a job but can\'t afford or find a place to rent. There are the vagabonds, who travel from place to place and the people who had to get out of a dangerous or abusive situation but had nowhere to go. There are the mentally ill, the physically disabled, the veterans with ptsd, the job loss victims, and the addicts. Then there is the tiniest percentage who you could probably consider lazy, they just have no interest in holding a job, although living on the streets is actually a lot of work. I\'ll get back to that later.\n\nYou can\'t group them all together because they all have different barriers to employment and help and you also can\'t just stick them all together because there are dangerous people as well as vulnerable people and families in need.\n\nAnother comment that shocked me was that he thought that there was plenty of help available, and all people needed to do was to go to a shelter or check into rehab, it\'s just that easy!\n\nIt makes me sadto learn that a lot ofpeople don\'t know how bad it has gotten over the years. Here in Canada there has been a steady decline in funding and continuous cuts and closures of facilities since before I was born. There are more and more people being kicked out into the cold and less and less help available. Most shelters are full, food banks are stretched thin and the waitlists for drug treatment programs can be incredibly long, even years.\n\nAnother common issue is that the shelters are unsafe for lot of people. You can\'t cram families, vulnerable women and elderly or disabled folks into a cramped space with a bunch of addicts and people with severe mental health issues and expect everything to be ok. Many people choose to stay away from shelters because rape, theft and violence are commonplace. If I was in that situation I\'d probably stay away as well.\n\nThe problems are varied and you can\'t solve everything with a few shelters or soup kitchens. I\'m not suggesting to just start handing out wads of cash without supports because that wouldn\'t solve much, but it\'s not an issue of being \"too lazy\". The issues are huge, varied and complicated but there are solutions and things we can do if we work together as a community. I will be sharing some of my ideas and things that some communities have done that have proven to be successful in a series of posts.\n\nFirst we have to understand the issues and challenges that each group faces, then we can look at options to help these people.\n\nFor the working homeless access to low income housing is a great barrier. Many of these people can and do get back on their feet with a little help and understanding. Many people who lost their jobs and then suffered the cascade effects of joblessness also do very well if they receive help in time.\n\nIf you have ever lost a job or a house then you should be able to empathize. You probably had supports of some kind, a spouse\'s income, a friend or family member who could take you in for a while or government funding such as disability or employment insurance. But what if you don\'t have anywhere to go or any way of getting funding? That\'s exactly how many people end up on the streets, and the longer they are out there the harder it is to get out of that situation. It takes a toll on the body, mind and spirit and thats when some people turn to substances to escape from the hopelessness.\n\nMost people have heard of the old work/experience paradox. You need the experience to get the job but you need the job to get the experience.\n\nWell, the job/home paradox is similar. You need the job to get the home but you need the home to apply for the jobs. Seriously, just try to hand out a resume without an address, they will toss your resume in the trash without a second thought.\n\nJust think of how hard it is for people to find work these days with an impeccable resume and a great outfit. Now picture how much harder it must be to impress someone when you haven\'t had a shower for a week, your clothes are ragged and smelly, and you don\'t have access to a computer or printer to even print a resume. Yes, there are free employment services available, but only if you have government issued ID and transportation to get there, which many people on the streets don\'t have.\n\nWith the automation of jobs as well as the decrease in stable full time opportunities available the problem is only going to get worse. Mix that in with inflation of living costs and the situation is getting more and more desperate every day. The working poor population is increasing rapidly and it doesn\'t take much to go from working poor to jobless, homeless and living on the streets if you don\'t have savingsor supports of any kind. People need to realize that not everyone on the streets is a drug addict or someone too lazy to find work. A large portion of them are ordinary people who hit hard times and couldn\'t get themselves back out of it.\n\nThere are many ideas which could help these people. One possible solution is the guaranteed basic universal income. One of the ideas that my friend shot down because he didn\'t want to pay for other people. There are of course issues and valid concerns with this idea and it hasn\'t been fully tested, but there are a few countries experimenting with it and it will be interesting to see the results. If I had a basic income I wouldn\'t just throw in the towel and spend the rest of my life laying on a beach, although that would be nice! The amounts are not high enough for everyone to just quit their jobs, but they would be enough to certainly help out struggling individuals and families and it could make the difference to keeping a home or buying groceries for a lot of people. What could you do with an extra few hundred to a thousand dollars a month? A lot if you stretch it and are careful! It would take some of the pressure off people but most would still have to work at least a bit. For people with disabilities and who can\'t work full time this could also help them to make ends meet. Instead of disability funding and EI we could all receive a bit of extra cash, enough to help us make it in todays increasingly expensive world. Ask the people from many Scandinavian countries and most will tell you that the higher taxes are not a burden at all and are appreciated for the high standards of living it allows them to have. Not everyone agrees of course, but the system we have now is failing millions of people and I believe it\'s time to try something new! It could be a blessing or a disaster, but we already have a disaster on our hands so...\n\nHave you heard of tiny houses?\n\nAnother awesome idea for struggling peopleis by building tiny house communities. Kind of like a trailer park these tiny houses aregrouped together and offer community support. There are already many projects underway and many have been incredibly successful. Adding things like a community garden and the tools and knowledge to grow food would also be a huge benefit. Sometimes all someone needs is a little help and space of their own to get back on their feet again.\n\n<a href=\"https://www.charterforcompassion.org/problem-solving/tiny-houses-for-the-homeless-an-affordable-solution-catches-on\" target=\"_blank\">Check out some of the projects here!</a>\n\nThere are so many issues and so many groups of people that I cannot possibly write about all of it in one blog post. I will be continuing this tangentwith a series of posts. Stay tuned for the next one!\n\nI welcome all comments and links to other amazing projects! Let me know whats happening in your community, or around the world that sparks your imagination!\n\nMuch love to you all! Cheers! :D','Homelessness - Understanding the problems','','trash','open','open','','__trashed-4','','','2017-04-17 18:33:04','2017-04-18 01:33:04','',0,'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/?p=47486',0,'post','',0),(47501,5,'2017-02-01 12:26:26','2017-02-01 20:26:26','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Thank You!</strong></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Your comments and questions are appreciated!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I will get back to you as soon as possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-47568\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/cat1-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"645\" height=\"450\" /></h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Thank You!','','publish','closed','closed','','thank-you','','','2017-03-05 22:45:11','2017-03-06 06:45:11','',0,'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/?page_id=47501',0,'page','',0),(47535,5,'2017-02-01 14:37:18','2017-02-01 22:37:18','<p>This is the WPForms preview page. All your form previews will be handled on this page.</p><p>The page is set to private, so it is not publically accessible. Please do not delete this page :) .</p>','WPForms Preview','','private','closed','closed','','wpforms-preview','','','2017-02-01 14:37:18','2017-02-01 22:37:18','',0,'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/wpforms-preview/',0,'page','',0),(47537,5,'2017-03-03 10:40:28','2017-03-03 18:40:28','<div class=\"crayon-plain-wrap\">\n<div id=\"crayon-58811faf85d42226995939-1\" class=\"crayon-line\">\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I\'m a front-end &amp; WordPress developer, blogger, artist and adventurer.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I\'m a free spirit with many interests and passions.\nI love new tech and grand ideas that are helping people to evolve towards a more sustainable relationship with our planet.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I\'m passionate about green living, camping, hiking and protecting this beautiful planet. I\'ll share things like cool new camping and trekking gear, awesome green living gadgets and ideas, essential oil recipesand delicious foods I like to bring outdoors. I\'ll also be sharing my ideas and thoughts about some of the big issues we face in this world and some of the solutions available, as well as some of my adventures.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Cheers!</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>','Hi, I\'m Natalie! I love building websites and adventures.','','inherit','closed','closed','','15-autosave-v1','','','2017-03-03 10:40:28','2017-03-03 18:40:28','',15,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/?p=47537',0,'revision','',0),(47540,5,'2017-02-02 05:58:24','2017-02-02 05:58:24','','Twitter','','publish','closed','closed','','twitter-2','','','2017-03-03 09:46:31','2017-03-03 17:46:31','',0,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/?p=47540',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(47547,1,'2017-02-02 05:59:07','2017-02-02 05:59:07','<p>This is the WPForms preview page. All your form previews will be handled on this page.</p><p>The page is set to private, so it is not publically accessible. Please do not delete this page :) .</p>','WPForms Preview','','private','closed','closed','','wpforms-preview-2','','','2017-02-02 05:59:07','2017-02-02 05:59:07','',0,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/?page_id=47547',0,'page','',0),(47558,5,'2017-02-02 20:16:46','2017-02-02 20:16:46',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','47558','','','2017-03-03 09:44:18','2017-03-03 17:44:18','',0,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/?p=47558',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(47559,5,'2017-02-02 20:16:46','2017-02-02 20:16:46',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','47559','','','2017-03-03 09:44:18','2017-03-03 17:44:18','',0,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/?p=47559',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(47560,5,'2017-02-02 20:20:07','2017-02-02 20:20:07','{\"id\":\"47560\",\"field_id\":3,\