talierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/campfire-1031141_1920.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(47637,5,'2017-03-03 10:15:37','2017-03-03 18:15:37','','denys-nevozhai-118879','','inherit','open','closed','','denys-nevozhai-118879','','','2017-03-03 10:15:37','2017-03-03 18:15:37','',47577,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/denys-nevozhai-118879.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(47638,5,'2017-03-03 10:16:26','2017-03-03 18:16:26','','bobby-burch-145906','','inherit','open','closed','','bobby-burch-145906','','','2017-03-03 10:16:26','2017-03-03 18:16:26','',47577,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/bobby-burch-145906.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(47640,5,'2017-03-03 10:20:10','2017-03-03 18:20:10','','fireworks-180553_1280','','inherit','open','closed','','fireworks-180553_1280','','','2017-03-03 10:20:10','2017-03-03 18:20:10','',47446,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/fireworks-180553_1280.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(47641,5,'2017-03-03 10:26:20','2017-03-03 18:26:20','','cream1','','inherit','open','closed','','cream1-2','','','2017-03-03 10:26:20','2017-03-03 18:26:20','',47600,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/cream1-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(47647,5,'2017-03-03 10:51:40','2017-03-03 18:51:40','http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/cropped-luca-bravo-189272-1.jpg','cropped-luca-bravo-189272-1.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-luca-bravo-189272-1-jpg','','','2017-03-03 10:51:40','2017-03-03 18:51:40','',0,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/cropped-luca-bravo-189272-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(47648,5,'2017-03-03 11:13:33','2017-03-03 19:13:33','Itchy skin.. omg the bane of my existence! I tend to be allergic to life, so a lot of things make me itch! Bug bites, plants, dusts, sawdusts, perfumes, moulds, dry skin, omg I could go on for ever! Luckily I have a wonderful back scratcher, but what to do when there\'s that annoying persistent itch that no amount ofscratching seems to cure? That\'s where itchy skin spray comes in super handy! I like to bring it camping and keep it in the bathroom for the rest of the time.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium alignleft\" src=\"https://media.giphy.com/media/3o7TKGhH4J3lEBN2a4/giphy.gif\" width=\"400\" height=\"275\" />','Itchy Skin Spray','','trash','open','open','','__trashed','','','2017-04-17 18:33:04','2017-04-18 01:33:04','',0,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/?p=47648',0,'post','',0),(47649,5,'2017-03-03 15:50:25','2017-03-03 23:50:25','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Who doesn\'t love good trick lists?! Personally, I\'m always a fan of simple things that make life a little easier. Some of these have saved my butt in the past, so I\'m passing on the knowledge. Hopefully you already know most of them, but if you don\'t then this is for you!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Hiking Tricks</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">1. We deal with a lot of rain out here on the wet coast, and nothing is worse than a soggy backpack and gear. Keep your stuff dry by lining your backpack with a garbage bag and keep the rain out! Bring another for an emergency poncho, it may not look super stylin\' but it works in a pinch.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47657 \" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Keener-9999-Pack-Liner-1024x655-1024x655.jpg\" width=\"770\" height=\"493\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://blog.rei.com/camp/22-camp-hacks-from-rei-experts/\">blog.rei.com</a></h6>\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: center;\"></h6>\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: center;\"></h6>\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: center;\"></h6>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">2. Use a thick ziplock baggie to keep your phone dry, most of the time you can still use it through the bag as well. Ive even taken some decent pictures through a new one. Or spend the money and invest in a proper waterproof case.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47651 aligncenter\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Phone-in-plastic-bag-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"720\" height=\"479\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.cs.usfca.edu/~cruse/RomaniaMinicourse/RomaniaFromAfar/ZipLocBag/ziplocbag.html\">www.cs.usfca.edu/</a></h6>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">3. Even if you are going for a short hike, bring duct tape!! It can save your feet from blisters or allow you to make emergency repairs. Store it on a flashlight, lighter, hiking pole, water bottle, or bring one of those little travel rolls. Duct tape, the answer is always duct tape!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-47652\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/211a4a678995842e4732a5ff5bee274e-261x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"261\" height=\"300\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://pinterest.com\">www.pinterest.com</a></h6>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">4. Bring binder clips so you can hang your wet items on your back pack to dry. No point in letting them stew in the bag. They also come in surprisingly handy for a lot of random things.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47653\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/enhanced-31679-1436217402-8-300x150.png\" width=\"916\" height=\"458\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h6 class=\"sub_buzz_source_via buzz_attribution\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://andrewskurka.com/2012/three-season-sock-systems/\" target=\"_blank\">andrewskurka.com</a></h6>\r\n<div class=\"sub_buzz_source_via buzz_attribution\" style=\"text-align: center;\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"sub_buzz_source_via buzz_attribution\" style=\"text-align: center;\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"sub_buzz_source_via buzz_attribution\" style=\"text-align: center;\"></div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">5. Bring a bandana! No one likes to see tp flowers on the trail, it\'s gross!!Use it as a pee rag thenfold it so the dirty is on the inside. You can either dry it in the sun (the UV rays will kill the bacteria) or rinse it in the next clean water source you find. Or if you want to keep trekking, store it in a plastic baggie until you can deal with it later.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47654\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/rainbow-full-of-bandanas-kym-backland-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"790\" height=\"593\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://runningfrompolarbears.wordpress.com/2016/03/12/pee-rag-say-whaaa/\">runningfrompolarbears.wordpress.com</a></h6>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">6. If you are travelling for a while, reinforce plastic baggies with duct tape. They will last much longer, are super light, and are much cheaper than going out and buying all the fancy bags. Plus they look really cool if you have fancy duct tape! Woo hoo!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47655\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/15e354c5f15a904348ecd2e4e9de00df-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"706\" height=\"706\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/736x/15/e3/54/15e354c5f15a904348ecd2e4e9de00df.jpg\">media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">7. Learn how to estimate remaining daylight, and always bring a flashlight. I can\'t tell you how many times this comes in handy on a lake or on a trail. If you don\'t know then study up!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47656\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/enhanced-buzz-13588-1375281419-26-282x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"918\" height=\"977\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://imgur.com/gallery/onira\">imgur.com/gallery/onira</a></h6>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">8. Have a pair of sacred socks! Sacred socks are clean, dry socks that live in your sleeping bag for sleeping purposes only.To keep your sleeping bag cleaner and less smelly, consider keeping a full set of sleeping clothes as sacred as well.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-47658\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Keener-0094-SacredSocks-1024x655-1024x655.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"655\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://blog.rei.com/camp/22-camp-hacks-from-rei-experts/\">blog.rei.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">9. If you have wet shoes or boots remove your insoles and stuff a dry shirt or some newspaper in your boots overnight to helpthem dry.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47660\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/how-to-dry-sneakers-running-shoes.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"841\" height=\"559\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.accordingtoelle.com/best-way-dry-wet-running-shoes/\"><span style=\"text-indent: 0em;\">www.accordingtoelle.com</span></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">10. The ol\' match behind the ear trick. Keep a match behind your ear when you head out on the trail. If you happen to get lost, your bag gets soaked, or your lighter bums out at least you will have one good dry match. This is a super old school trick that I can\'t remember who told me about way back in the day.. Luckily I\'ve never needed it, but it\'s a good one to remember. No pics for this one! lol!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">11. Butt Pads! They literally save your butt! At first I thought they were stupid when I first heard of them,butt I bring mineeverywhere now. It\'s super handy to be able to sit anywhere even in the rain or on soggy logs or rocks. If you don\'t have a butt pad then grab a regular plastic bag to sit on and you won\'t get your pants wet! I also sometimes bring a bag for my butt pad to keep it dryer. Yes to dry cushiness!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-47699\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/845302.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"440\" height=\"274\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.rei.com/product/845302/rei-co-op-sit-pad\">rei.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">12. Bread bags are the perfect size for holding most water bottles. Slip your bottle inside, twist the top, secure with something like a clip or elastic band, and you are slightly safer from spills in your pack.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-47700\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/61OLGNG2BBL._SX522_.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"522\" height=\"232\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.amazon.in/Blue-Donuts-Clear-Bread-Food/dp/B00JH73LAS\">amazon.in</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">13. If your feet start to get sore in certain areas, sometimes the pain can be alleviated by lacing your boots differently. Learn lacing techniques to keep you on the trails.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-47698\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/REI_Expert_Advice-Boot_Lacing_Tips-336x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"336\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.rei.com/learn/expert-advice/lacing-hiking-boots.html?cm_mmc=sm_pn-_-expertadvice&amp;crlt.pid=camp.1X09InFvCJrn\">rei.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Have fun out there!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Cheers!</p>','13 Awesome Hiking Tricks I Love','','publish','open','open','','awesome-hiking-tricks-to-make-life-easier','','','2017-03-07 09:35:26','2017-03-07 17:35:26','',0,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/?p=47649',0,'post','',0),(47651,5,'2017-03-03 13:59:54','2017-03-03 21:59:54','','Phone-in-plastic-bag','','inherit','open','closed','','phone-in-plastic-bag','','','2017-03-03 13:59:54','2017-03-03 21:59:54','',47649,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Phone-in-plastic-bag.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(47652,5,'2017-03-03 14:03:38','2017-03-03 22:03:38','','211a4a678995842e4732a5ff5bee274e','','inherit','open','closed','','211a4a678995842e4732a5ff5bee274e','','','2017-03-03 14:03:38','2017-03-03 22:03:38','',47649,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/211a4a678995842e4732a5ff5bee274e.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(47653,5,'2017-03-03 14:09:12','2017-03-03 22:09:12','','enhanced-31679-1436217402-8','','inherit','open','closed','','enhanced-31679-1436217402-8','','','2017-03-03 14:09:12','2017-03-03 22:09:12','',47649,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/enhanced-31679-1436217402-8.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(47654,5,'2017-03-03 14:12:32','2017-03-03 22:12:32','','rainbow-full-of-bandanas-kym-backland','','inherit','open','closed','','rainbow-full-of-bandanas-kym-backland','','','2017-03-03 14:12:32','2017-03-03 22:12:32','',47649,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/rainbow-full-of-bandanas-kym-backland.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(47655,5,'2017-03-03 14:24:51','2017-03-03 22:24:51','','15e354c5f15a904348ecd2e4e9de00df','','inherit','open','closed','','15e354c5f15a904348ecd2e4e9de00df','','','2017-03-03 14:24:51','2017-03-03 22:24:51','',47649,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/15e354c5f15a904348ecd2e4e9de00df.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(47656,5,'2017-03-03 14:29:37','2017-03-03 22:29:37','','enhanced-buzz-13588-1375281419-26','','inherit','open','closed','','enhanced-buzz-13588-1375281419-26','','','2017-03-03 14:29:37','2017-03-03 22:29:37','',47649,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/enhanced-buzz-13588-1375281419-26.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(47657,5,'2017-03-03 14:33:33','2017-03-03 22:33:33','','Keener-9999-Pack-Liner-1024x655','','inherit','open','closed','','keener-9999-pack-liner-1024x655','','','2017-03-03 14:33:33','2017-03-03 22:33:33','',47649,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Keener-9999-Pack-Liner-1024x655.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(47658,5,'2017-03-03 14:38:06','2017-03-03 22:38:06','','Keener-0094-SacredSocks-1024x655','','inherit','open','closed','','keener-0094-sacredsocks-1024x655','','','2017-03-03 14:38:06','2017-03-03 22:38:06','',47649,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Keener-0094-SacredSocks-1024x655.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(47660,5,'2017-03-03 14:40:41','2017-03-03 22:40:41','','how-to-dry-sneakers-running-shoes','','inherit','open','closed','','how-to-dry-sneakers-running-shoes','','','2017-03-03 14:40:41','2017-03-03 22:40:41','',47649,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/how-to-dry-sneakers-running-shoes.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(47663,5,'2017-03-03 15:50:11','2017-03-03 23:50:11','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Who doesn\'t love some good tricks?! I\'ve used manyof these many times andcan swear by them, the rest I\'m super stoked about trying! Some of these are probably common knowledge, but here\'s a list of my favouritesI\'ve learned over time!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Camping Tricks</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">1. Pitch your tent with the door facing the wind to discourage bugs from congregating.</p>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-47664\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/camping-1031360_1920-1024x680.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"680\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">2. Make travel coffee or tea bags out of coffee filters and dental floss, or you can usually find small loose leaf tea pouches in a dollar or grocery store that work well too.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-47665\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/c849da9f110d3eb1eb8754c7f8683d50.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"736\" height=\"588\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.pinterest.com\">pinterest.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">3. Line your pie ironwith tinfoil to make it easier to clean.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47666 \" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/2012-06-03-17.11.40-e1488588453952-727x1024.jpg\" width=\"505\" height=\"711\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://goingfreeglutendairy.blogspot.com/2012/06/wonderful-wednesday-pie-irons.html\">goingfreeglutendairy.blogspot.com</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">4. Wrap your meats in cabbage leaves then tinfoil to keep from burning.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47667 size-full\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/a8a1b1a54e67f28875b41945e7e31028-e1488582069132.jpg\" width=\"386\" height=\"467\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.pinterest.com\">pinterest.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">5. Fix a broken tarp with a rock.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47668\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/DE3081936-Q3-1-Facebook-hack2-1200-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"575\" height=\"575\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.pinterest.com\">pinterest.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">6. Use a stick so you don\'t have to cut your rope.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47669\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/enhanced-buzz-27474-1396992113-18.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"536\" height=\"714\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.lifehack.org/articles/lifestyle/30-brilliant-camping-hacks-wish-knew-earlier.html\">www.lifehack.org</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">7. Save up your bread tabs and use them as lightweight clothes pins to hang your clothes. They work perfectly on most sized ropes!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47670\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/DE3081936-Q3-1-Facebook-hack1-1200-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"728\" height=\"728\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://blog.rei.com/camp/22-camp-hacks-from-rei-experts/\">blog.rei.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">8. Apply a little candle wax or bar soap to zippers to keep them zipping properly.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47672\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/candle-wax-for-stuck-zipper.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"806\" height=\"452\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.wetellyouhow.com/convert-waste-into-useful-household-things/\">www.wetellyouhow.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">9. Add a little glow in the dark rope or stringto the zippers to make themeasy to find in the middle of the night.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47673\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/diy-zipper-pull.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"622\" height=\"467\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://theultimatehang.com/2013/04/diy-lightweight-zipper-pulls/\">theultimatehang.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">10. Use a shower cap to keep your sandals and shoes from soaking up moisture, (make sure they are under the vestibule though!), also helps to keep things clean when packing up.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-47674\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/shoecap1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"480\" height=\"640\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://everydaysparks.com/tag/shower-cap/\">everydaysparks.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">11. Instead of dealing with liquids, buy some solid shampoo and conditioner bars. I get mine from lush, but there are other options as well; you can even make your own if you are talented! They are small and last forever and you don\'t have to worry about spills or lugging huge bottles around. Just make sure you leave the tin open for a few hours so they dry out again and you are good to go!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-47675\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Lush_003.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"720\" height=\"480\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.alexinwanderland.com/2014/06/04/solid-shampoo-for-travelers/\">www.alexinwanderland.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">12. Shave soap into single use flakes and store them in a baggie so you don\'t have to deal with soggy bar messes.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-47676\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/bbf56ea96f40e2f605972b2f75e4a500.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"550\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/291397038362425228/\">pinterest.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">13. If you don\'t have access to a shower, bring two different coloured face cloths. Boil some water in the morning, let it cool a little, and wash your face with one first, don\'t double dip! So nice and warm in the cold mornings! :D Then wash your other smelly regions with the other. Rinse then dry in the sunlight to kill bacteria. Clean them with a flake of soap if you are staying for a long time, and thats all you need! Just remember which colour is for your face! lol!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47677 \" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/stack-of-colorful-wash-cloths-e1488583416993.jpg\" width=\"765\" height=\"487\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.wisegeek.com/what-are-face-cloths.htm\">www.wisegeek.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">14. Freeze bottles and use them in your cooler instead of ice, or better yet make some iced tea and freeze it! Keeps your cooler cool and less messy, lasts longer than ice and you will have cold drinks when they melt.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-47678\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ice_water_bottles_featured-620x330-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"620\" height=\"330\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://50campfires.com/frozen-water-bottles-in-your-cooler/\">50campfires.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">15. Line your cooler with insulated reflective foam (like the windshield screens) to make things stay cooler longer, or make a cooler cover!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"wp-image-47679 aligncenter\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/b105b117cf5eb0ca8eadbb8ee28d7cbe.jpg\" width=\"544\" height=\"408\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.pinterest.com\">pinterest.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">16. Bring a couple of gardeners\' foam kneeling pads if you have a crawl in tent. Stick one outside and one inside the door to save your knees! They are cheap, light and easy to store or move where you need them. Your bruised knees with thank you!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47681\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/30-w-dotsSm.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"451\" height=\"345\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://katzgardengloves.com/index.php?main_page=product_info&amp;cPath=7_88&amp;products_id=450\">katzgardengloves.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">17. Instead of hauling around fragile whole eggs, put them in a large bottle or hard boil them.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-47682\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/2-Scrambled-Eggs-in-a-Bottle.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"612\" height=\"816\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.pinterest.com\">pinterest.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">17. Use a mesh bag and hang your clean dishes to dry.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-47683\" src=\"http://natalierose.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/714CoZ3p-L._SL1088_-1024x809.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"772\" height=\"610\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.pinterest.com\">pinterest.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">18. Forgot your can opener? Learn how to open cans without one!</p>\r\nhttps://youtu.be/oH2NahLjx-Y\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHave fun out there!\r\n\r\n~ Cheers!','18 Awesome Camping Tricks To Make Camp Life Easier','','publish','open','open','','awesome-camping-tricks-to-make-life-easier','','','2017-03-07 09:45:16','2017-03-07 17:45:16','',0,'http://natalierose.wpengine.com/?p=47663',0,'post','',0),(47664,5,'2017-03-03 14:53:36','2017-03-03 22:53:36','','camping-1031360_1920','','inherit','open','closed','